  "prompt": "What mobile game is best?",
  "response": "The \"best\" mobile game really depends on your personal preferences, but here are some highly popular and critically acclaimed mobile games across different genres:\n\n1. **Action/Adventure:**\n   - **Genshin Impact** - An open-world action RPG with stunning visuals and a vast world to explore.\n   - **Call of Duty: Mobile** - A first-person shooter that brings the classic Call of Duty experience to mobile.\n\n2. **Strategy:**\n   - **Clash Royale** - A real-time strategy game where you collect and upgrade cards featuring troops, spells, and defenses.\n   - **Plants vs. Zombies 2** - A tower defense game where you use plants to fend off waves of zombies.\n\n3. **Puzzle:**\n   - **Monument Valley** - A visually stunning puzzle game with Escher-like architecture and fluid mechanics.\n   - **The Room series** - A series of intricate puzzle games with a mysterious narrative.\n\n4. **Simulation:**\n   - **The Sims Mobile** - A life simulation game where you create and control characters in a virtual world.\n   - **Stardew Valley** - A farming simulation game that allows you to build and manage your own farm.\n\n5. **Multiplayer Online Battle Arena (MOBA):**\n   - **MOBAs:** Games like **Mobile Legends: Bang Bang** and **Arena of Valor** offer fast-paced, team-based battles.\n\n6. **Casual:**\n   - **Candy Crush Saga** - A match-three puzzle game with hundreds of levels.\n   - **Among Us** - A social deduction game where players work together to complete tasks while trying to identify the impostors.\n\n7. **Role-Playing Games (RPG):**\n   - **Honkai Impact 3rd** - A fast-paced action RPG with a strong narrative and character development.\n   - **Fire Emblem Heroes** - A tactical RPG featuring characters from the Fire Emblem series.\n\nIf you're looking for something specific, feel free to ask, and I can tailor recommendations further!",
